we never made assault.

22:30.760 --> 22:33.103
If you are innocent,
you have nothing to fear.

22:34.160 --> 22:36.264
I will vouch for you in court tomorrow.

22:37.480 --> 22:38.583
(Signs)

22:42.440 --> 22:44.180
Say naught of this to Sister.

22:44.360 --> 22:45.748
How can I keep it from her?

22:45.920 --> 22:48.866
You swear,
they who be innocent shall be free?

22:51.680 --> 22:52.817
Yes.

22:53.000 --> 22:57.460
Then it profit her not to know we're arrested
when tomorrow we'll be free again.

23:17.040 --> 23:19.463
(Honking)

23:29.240 --> 23:31.299
Was it very bad?

23:32.440 --> 23:33.543
Yes.

23:41.240 --> 23:43.219
No. I must go out again.

23:44.560 --> 23:46.107
There were arrests.

23:46.280 --> 23:48.259
Men are due in court at midday.

23:50.040 --> 23:52.019
What can I do?

23:54.920 --> 23:56.899
Lie with me awhile.

24:12.040 --> 24:14.019
I must go.

24:17.120 --> 24:19.099
Keep home today.

24:19.760 --> 24:22.820
There's unrest in the villages.
I would have you safe.

24:28.840 --> 24:30.944
My dear, I'm just leaving for the court.

24:31.120 --> 24:32.621
Was not the trial at midday?

24:32.800 --> 24:34.859
Oh, I ordered it to be brought forward.

24:35.040 --> 24:37.941
Best to have such matters
resolved early In the day.

24:42.760 --> 24:44.341
(He makes an animal noise)

24:47.600 --> 24:51.024
- Could it be true?
- Sam and Drake claim they're innocent.

24:51.200 --> 24:53.782
Jago throttled a corn merchant
but swears he left him alive.

24:56.440 --> 24:58.499
Reliable witnesses?

24:58.680 --> 25:01.945
Those in the pay of
the Honourable Member for Truro.

25:02.200 --> 25:04.418
You think George is behind the charges?

25:04.600 --> 25:06.181
7'0 Drake, 5am and Jags?

25:06.360 --> 25:07.941
Without question.

25:08.120 --> 25:12.625
- Such a man is our Member of Parliament?
- Until Hugh defeats him at the election.

25:14.880 --> 25:16.097
(Clears his throat)

25:16.280 --> 25:17.986
In truth, I think Hugh a good man.

25:23.560 --> 25:26.506
Pity we'll see so little of him
if he goes to Westminster.

25:26.680 --> 25:29.342
He'll be absent from Cornwall
for most of the year.

25:39.880 --> 25:42.144
(Chains rattling)

25:46.040 --> 25:47.860
(He chuckles softly)

25:54.680 --> 25:56.500
Where is everyone?

25:56.680 --> 25:58.545
Captain Ross, Dr Enys and the rest?

25:58.720 --> 26:00.699
Captain Ross did say he'd be here.

26:05.760 --> 26:08.945
- Mr Ross gone to Truro?
- No peace for the wicked.

26:12.160 --> 26:14.139
I think maybe he's not that wicked.

26:16.560 --> 26:21.429
Indeed, I clearly wish I'd never telled 'ee
what I saw that day at Sawle church.

26:23.120 --> 26:25.099
Prudie...

26:27.400 --> 26:29.664
It...'twas not on that account that I...

26:31.920 --> 26:34.059
...that Hugh and I...

26:37.880 --> 26:41.509
Indeed, I can scarce account
for what happened at all.

26:44.120 --> 26:48.625
All I know is, a handsome young poet

26:48.800 --> 26:51.780
beguiled me...and I him.

26:53.680 --> 26:56.945
And we shared...a moment...

26:58.520 --> 27:00.499
...then parted.

27:01.280 --> 27:03.259
And that's the end of it.

27:13.640 --> 27:17.019
Prisoners, the court will now move
to place sentencing upon you.

27:17.200 --> 27:21.739
You who stand here today
guilty of riotous assembly...

27:21.920 --> 27:24.627
know that the full rigour of the law
must be applied...

27:24.800 --> 27:26.119
They've already been tried.

27:26.280 --> 27:29.864
...and would surely be so were it not
for the plea made on your behalf

27:30.040 --> 27:31.746
by my Lord de Dunstanville.

27:31.920 --> 27:33.103
It would appear so.

27:33.280 --> 27:36.067
George must have arranged
for the hearing to be brought forward.

27:36.240 --> 27:39.220
In consideration of which,
you will forthwith be released.

27:39.400 --> 27:41.379
(Relieved sighs)

27:42.280 --> 27:46.944
You who have been found guilty of more
serious crimes can expect no such mercy.

27:47.120 --> 27:51.068
Examples must be set,
a clear message sent out

27:51.240 --> 27:54.380
so that others considering
a repeat of these transgressions

27:54.560 --> 27:56.983
may know what lies in store for them.

27:58.320 --> 28:03.303
Michael Penhale,
Mark Pinner, John Hoskin...

28:03.480 --> 28:06.347
you are sentenced
to seven years' transportation.

28:06.520 --> 28:08.226
(Muttering)

28:10.400 --> 28:12.379
Jago Martin,

28:12.560 --> 28:14.221
Samuel Came,

28:14.400 --> 28:15.742
Drake Came,

28:15.920 --> 28:19.139
you will be taken from this court to prison...

28:20.040 --> 28:24.022
...and thence to a place of execution
where you will be hanged from the neck

28:24.200 --> 28:26.179
- until you be dead.
- No!

28:27.680 --> 28:28.704
(Grunting)

28:28.880 --> 28:30.268
(Sam mutters a prayer)

28:30.440 --> 28:32.419
Get back in line!

28:38.000 --> 28:40.343
DWIGHT: Ross, come away.

28:41.800 --> 28:43.381
Ross.

28:46.400 --> 28:48.425
Divine justice has spoken.

28:48.600 --> 28:52.900
Following the riots of last night,
three miserable souls will hang.

28:53.600 --> 28:55.227
- I pity them.
- Do not.

28:55.400 --> 28:57.504
They are criminals of the vilest kind.

28:58.040 --> 29:00.941
I shall urge them to repent
as they mount the scaffold.

29:01.120 --> 29:03.907
- But since they are Methodists...
- Methodists?

29:05.400 --> 29:06.822
Do you know their names?

29:07.000 --> 29:08.422
Nor do I wish to.

29:08.600 --> 29:10.977
It's bad enough that I must pray for their souls.

29:19.920 --> 29:21.899
(Breathes tensely)

29:25.040 --> 29:27.019
(Chains rattling)

