53:43.880 --> 53:46.747
something feverish in his demeanour.

53:46.920 --> 53:50.504
Were that all,
I'd say there was no cause for concern.

53:50.680 --> 53:55.617
But...if the fever is symptomatic
of some other condition,

53:55.800 --> 53:57.779
along with the headaches...

53:59.000 --> 54:00.262
It's strange, though.

54:00.440 --> 54:05.423
I thought him so much more robust than I
and now he ails and I grow stronger.

54:09.280 --> 54:12.784
Strong enough to consider
an addition to our household?

54:15.040 --> 54:16.507
Do you mean...?

54:20.160 --> 54:21.661
(Dog growls softly)

54:26.840 --> 54:28.819
(Barks)

54:33.200 --> 54:36.067
My dear, can your election plans
wait for another night?

54:36.240 --> 54:38.424
Perhaps you could attend to your wife.

54:45.240 --> 54:47.219
Or must she attend to you?

54:59.400 --> 55:01.265
Ross.

55:01.440 --> 55:03.863
- I thought maybe you'd stay in Truro.
- Demelza.

55:04.040 --> 55:05.701
I must tell you...

55:05.880 --> 55:07.745
there was a hanging.

55:07.920 --> 55:08.989
Dear God.

55:09.160 --> 55:11.025
Three sentenced, two reprieved.

55:11.200 --> 55:13.179
Who was it?

55:58.680 --> 56:00.227
How was Hugh?

56:03.320 --> 56:05.538
He seemed a little...fragile.

56:07.440 --> 56:09.021
But still in love with you?

56:11.040 --> 56:12.746
I think so.

56:14.600 --> 56:15.817
And you?

56:17.360 --> 56:20.261
I'm grieved for him -
that his health is so uncertain.

56:22.680 --> 56:25.467
They say pity is akin to love.

56:26.080 --> 56:27.786
I don't think it's pity he wants.

56:27.960 --> 56:30.178
They say it's the last thing a man wants.

56:31.400 --> 56:32.822
Or a woman.

56:38.720 --> 56:40.699
Did you pity me
when you left me for Elizabeth?

56:40.880 --> 56:43.940
- I never left you.
- It seemed to me like you did.

56:45.000 --> 56:46.388
That night.

56:47.680 --> 56:49.147
And the day you met her at the church.

56:49.320 --> 56:52.824
I never told you at the time because I
didn't trust myself to find the words.

56:53.000 --> 56:55.980
- To say you still loved her?
- No. The reverse.

56:58.000 --> 57:00.582
I loved her once, as well you know,

57:02.760 --> 57:06.105
and there's a part of me that will always
think of her with affection but...

57:07.280 --> 57:12.820
...I realised that day that she never was,
and never could be, what you are to me.

57:16.000 --> 57:17.467
Indispensable.

57:20.600 --> 57:22.067
Irreplaceable.

57:24.440 --> 57:26.419
You tell me this now because...?

57:26.600 --> 57:28.977
I think perhaps I've taken you for granted.

57:30.360 --> 57:34.262
Assumed you knew...
what to me was obvious.

57:34.440 --> 57:36.419
That you are the better part of me.

57:37.360 --> 57:39.817
I think perhaps I've been guilty of the same.

57:44.240 --> 57:46.219
Oh, Ross...

57:47.440 --> 57:50.341
...how can it be that two people
who love so much...

57:50.520 --> 57:52.829
Understand so little?

58:01.440 --> 58:03.419
Is it now too late?

58:11.880 --> 58:13.780
I hope not.
